I have a similar issue, but MXnet is far behind both on powerful PC and on Raspberry PI. 
Namely, on PC I have 17.38ms per image for MXNet and around 4ms for Caffe. On Raspberry PI - 369.55ms per image for MXNet and 76.53ms for Caffe. The network is identical for both setups, I converted it from the Caffe model.

I am using MXNet.cpp API. The benchmark code looks like this:

```
        vector<float> img_data(img_size * batch_size, 0.5);
        img.SyncCopyFromCPU(img_data);
        NDArray::WaitAll();
        m_argsMap["data"] = img;

        Executor *executor =
            m_net.SimpleBind(global_ctx, m_argsMap, map<string, NDArray>(),
                             map<string, OpReqType>(), m_auxMap);

        CHECK_NOTNULL(executor);

        std::vector<long> timings;
        for (int i = 0; i < NUM_EVAL; ++i) {
            auto start = std::chrono::system_clock::now();

            executor->Forward(false);
            NDArray::WaitAll();
            auto end = std::chrono::system_clock::now();
            timings.push_back(
                std::chrono::duration_cast<std::chrono::milliseconds>(
                    end - start).count());
        }

        report_metrics(timings, batch_size);
```

